data.description:
Motivated Seller!  We just had it appraised and the 3 homes on 3 acres on the large White Creek that can be kayaked on, and also has RV hook ups is listed BELOW the recent appraisal! 1st house has 4 bedrooms, 2 baths, 2nd house has 1 bedroom/studio, 3rd house has 2 bedrooms and 2 baths! Adventure is calling from your new private retreat that is Nestled within ''The Bluffs at White Creek'' gated community in Deer Lodge, TN.  This unique serene getaway spans 2.96 acres that overlooks the beautiful White Creek that feeds into the Obed River, and an additional studio home/bungalow.  There is also a custom built wooden playground amongst the homes! This retreat has something for everyone! This retreat is ideally located within an hour to Knoxville but has the feeling of a world away and offers a haven for families and adventure seekers alike, with both tranquility and thrilling outdoor activities. 

You won't be disappointed with the Obed Scenic River and Frozen Head State Park just a short drive away, as well as Windrock mountain that accommodates all types of recreational vehicles from ATVs, SxS, Dirt bikes, Mountain Bikes, Jeeps, 4x4's, buggies and more!  It is known to be the largest privately owned riding area in the country! Embark on thrilling adventures in the great outdoors, exploring the rivers and trails that this region has to offer.

The main house is a spacious 3708 sq ft haven with vaulted ceilings, providing a grand ambiance. Featuring 4 bedrooms and 2.5 baths, this residence ensures ample space for the entire family. The master suite is a luxurious retreat complete with a claw foot tub and a fireplace, perfect for cozying up during the cool fall days. An additional upstairs loft offers versatile space for various activities. The kitchen boasts gorgeous cabinets and skylights, providing an abundance of natural light. A large screened porch wraps around two sides of the house, allowing you to soak in the peaceful surroundings. An attached garage and expansive wood decks add to the convenience and charm of this main house.

Located just down the hill from the main house is the charming "Gray tin house" with vaulted ceilings, gorgeous entertaining space, large screened in deck overlooking White Creek as well as offering 2 bedrooms and 1 bathroom. Across from the main house, you'll find a versatile bungalow style home that can serve as guest quarters or a pool house, adding flexibility to your living arrangements.

Immerse yourself in nature's tranquility as you sit on one of the many screened porches, listening to the gentle sound of the creek rippling by. The property features large exposed boulders, creating a picturesque setting. Take a leisurely stroll down to the creek for relaxation or follow the paved path leading to the neighboring area. Must-see both properties to fully appreciate the beauty and potential they hold.

High-speed internet is available from Highland Telephone Company, ensuring that you can stay connected even in this peaceful retreat. Additionally, adventure enthusiasts will be thrilled to know that rock climbing and white water rafting opportunities await at the nearby Obed. Hiking and camping enthusiasts will also delight in the proximity to Frozen Head State Park.

For investors seeking a unique opportunity, this property presents excellent potential. Please note that the houses have some deferred maintenance and will require repairs. The property will be sold "as is," allowing buyers to tailor the repairs and renovations to their preferences.

With its abundance of wildlife and native East Tennessee plants, this property presents an excellent opportunity to create an Airbnb rental or a private retreat for your family. Don't miss out on this remarkable chance to embrace the beauty and adventure awaiting you at this secluded oasis  at The Bluffs at White Creek. 

Buyers to verify SF, HOA information, Rooms, and all other information.
